      "writtenOn": "2020-08-06T12:10:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Wouldn\u0027t a dedicated ttlcache be a better fit here? Let\u0027s assume 1k tiles (256k commits, i.e. all of time for most projects) have a paramset in memory at any given time and a paramset has 100 keys with 10 values each at 100 bytes. That\u0027s 100M of RAM, which should be plenty small w/o needing to also evict based on number of entries.",
